15:35.002 --> 15:38.842
Oh, come, now. On what grounds?

15:38.843 --> 15:41.013
This ridiculous van.

15:41.014 --> 15:44.687
It smells like patchouli.
It's lined with hemp.

15:44.688 --> 15:47.793
Beg your pardon? I got a
very good deal on it.

15:47.794 --> 15:51.099
You own this revolting jalopy?

15:51.100 --> 15:54.507
Oh, I traded my diamond and
pearl earrings for it.

15:54.508 --> 15:57.278
Is this what a midlife
crisis looks like?

15:57.279 --> 16:00.385
I prefer to think of it as an awakening.

16:03.959 --> 16:05.462
(GROANS)

16:05.463 --> 16:07.265
This is an urgent message
for Mrs. Landsman.

16:07.266 --> 16:08.802
If Dr. Leveau attempts to contact you,

16:08.803 --> 16:10.806
you should know she will
be violating the law.

16:10.807 --> 16:12.008
Please call us back.

16:12.009 --> 16:13.611
And we want six keys. Six only.

16:13.612 --> 16:15.749
All stamped "Do Not Duplicate."

16:15.750 --> 16:20.760
<i>♪♪♪</i>

16:31.347 --> 16:33.150
Nancy, it's Barton.

16:33.151 --> 16:35.989
Hoping to speak to you. This is...

16:35.990 --> 16:38.528
<i>Well, it's all very
confused here right now.</i>

16:38.529 --> 16:41.032
<i>I suppose I'm hoping that what Art said</i>

16:41.033 --> 16:45.842
<i>to Bill and Virginia about
your plans about...</i>

16:45.843 --> 16:47.813
<i>I trust it's not true</i>

16:47.814 --> 16:50.017
<i>and that you can straighten this out.</i>

16:50.018 --> 16:53.090
<i>So please. Please call me.</i>

16:53.091 --> 16:54.026
<i>This is very...</i>

16:56.030 --> 16:59.036
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

17:01.442 --> 17:03.177
Dr. Nancy Leveau?

17:03.178 --> 17:05.182
We have a warrant here
to search the premises.

17:12.162 --> 17:14.867
Look, you're not expecting me
to invite you in, are you?

17:14.867 --> 17:17.906
I don't need an invitation.
I have a warrant.

17:21.848 --> 17:25.087
You do know that the second you
step foot in your new clinic

17:25.088 --> 17:26.991
and use one word of our protocol

17:26.992 --> 17:28.995
or attempt to treat any of our patients

17:28.996 --> 17:30.999
or publish a book using
any of our research,

17:31.000 --> 17:34.005
we will come after you, Nancy,

17:34.006 --> 17:37.078
so fast, your doors will
close before they even open.

17:37.079 --> 17:38.915
On what grounds?

17:38.916 --> 17:40.785
I mean, you closing our doors.

17:40.786 --> 17:42.556
Not only can we open our own clinic.

17:42.557 --> 17:44.058
We can also say we trained

17:44.059 --> 17:47.064
at the Masters and Johnson
Institute, because we did.

17:47.065 --> 17:48.568
You might want to check with Art

17:48.569 --> 17:51.307
before you get too cozy as a "we."

17:52.309 --> 17:53.878
Legally, you have nothing.

17:53.879 --> 17:55.916
I never signed that
nondisclosure agreement.

17:55.917 --> 17:59.289
Hmm, so your conscience is clear.

17:59.290 --> 18:00.992
Like a shark doesn't think twice

18:00.993 --> 18:02.930
about the thing it chews up in its path

18:02.931 --> 18:05.000
because that's just what sharks do.

18:05.001 --> 18:07.573
And who would understand that
better than you, Virginia?

18:07.574 --> 18:09.577
You know, we are very
similar, you and I,

18:09.578 --> 18:11.581
except that I know where
this winds up for me.

18:11.582 --> 18:12.883
I will end up alone,

18:12.884 --> 18:14.954
and I have made my peace with that.

18:14.955 --> 18:17.391
What you don't see is, you
will end up alone too.

18:17.392 --> 18:19.897
Oh, well, that's another
miscalculation on your part

18:19.898 --> 18:22.903
because Bill and I...
we're getting married,

18:22.904 --> 18:25.307
so while you'll end up on your own,

18:25.308 --> 18:27.813
newly divorced and mired in lawsuits,

18:27.814 --> 18:31.119
we will be the poster
couple for sex therapy.

18:31.120 --> 18:32.889
Excuse me, Mrs. Johnson?

18:32.890 --> 18:34.560
I'll need you to verify any property

18:34.561 --> 18:37.432
that might belong to you or
the clinic as I proceed.

18:37.433 --> 18:39.003
Excuse me.

18:44.914 --> 18:48.020
You won't find anything, Virginia.

18:48.021 --> 18:51.927
Not your property, not
even your happy ending.

18:51.928 --> 18:55.535
So he was just sitting there,
cooking on a little hibachi,

18:55.536 --> 18:57.304
but it wasn't until one of his students

18:57.305 --> 19:00.278
told me who we was that
we actually spoke.

19:01.648 --> 19:03.651
You're still thinking about work?

19:03.652 --> 19:05.287
I'm sorry.

19:05.288 --> 19:07.391
It's just been a day,
but it's your turn.

19:07.392 --> 19:10.665
So, uh, there he is...

19:10.666 --> 19:13.571
- BOTH:  Dr. Phillips.
- LIBBY:  <i>The</i> law guru.

19:13.572 --> 19:16.644
Squatting in a field,
listening to Joan...

19:16.645 --> 19:19.850
- "Bay-ez"?
- Baez.

19:19.851 --> 19:21.119
Grilling hot dogs.

19:21.120 --> 19:24.125
Grilling mushrooms
from the woods nearby.

19:24.126 --> 19:26.262
Oh, that sounds potentially fatal.

19:26.263 --> 19:29.202
(LAUGHS) My point is, Dr. Phillips,

19:29.203 --> 19:32.609
Professor Emeritus of
Public Law at Berkeley...

19:32.610 --> 19:35.882
he sat me down on that tarp
and he encouraged me...

19:35.883 --> 19:38.353
well, actually, he inspired me

19:38.354 --> 19:41.894
to come out and enroll.

19:41.895 --> 19:44.298
He even pulled some
strings on my behalf.

19:44.299 --> 19:48.240
- Enroll? In...
- Uh, law school.

19:48.241 --> 19:50.712
Dr. Phillips says there
is no greater calling

19:50.713 --> 19:51.814
than the law.

19:51.815 --> 19:53.216
I mean, forget the local college

19:53.217 --> 19:56.055
where it'll take me six
years to get my JD.

19:56.056 --> 19:59.930
No, I have to take up the law
with an undiminished passion.

19:59.931 --> 20:01.500
- Dr. Phillips says that I...
- I'm sorry.

20:01.501 --> 20:04.038
Just forget Dr. Phillips for one second.

20:04.039 --> 20:06.176
What... what are you saying?

20:06.177 --> 20:09.750
Law school in-in Berkeley?

20:09.751 --> 20:11.587
- Mm-hmm.
- California?

20:11.588 --> 20:14.426
Libby, how would you
look after the kids?

20:14.427 --> 20:16.631
They would come with me, of course.

20:18.134 --> 20:19.269
What? No. You...

20:21.106 --> 20:22.742
You can't take my children.

20:22.743 --> 20:25.214
I'm not taking <i>our</i> children.

20:25.215 --> 20:27.619
We would make time for you
to come out and visit.

20:27.620 --> 20:28.955
We would come back here regularly.

20:28.956 --> 20:31.125
You can't be serious.

20:31.126 --> 20:34.933
It has taken me years... decades...

20:34.934 --> 20:38.441
to finally discover some path forward,

20:38.442 --> 20:39.810
a way to find happiness.

20:39.811 --> 20:41.513
And I am very glad for you.

20:41.514 --> 20:45.087
And now it is time for my
life to fall into place too.

20:45.088 --> 20:46.690
Which is something you can do here!

20:46.691 --> 20:48.961
Jesus, you can't just
drop this piece of news

20:48.962 --> 20:50.698
into polite chitchat.

20:50.699 --> 20:52.769
- What are you thinking?
- Oh, my God. Here we go.

20:52.770 --> 20:55.140
Are you honestly gonna make
me fight you for our kids?

20:55.141 --> 20:56.477
I'm sorry. Fight?

20:56.478 --> 20:58.313
I have no intention of fighting you.

20:58.314 --> 20:59.650
And what will the kids think
if I don't fight for them?

20:59.651 --> 21:01.019
That I don't care about them?

21:01.020 --> 21:02.288
That I don't love them?

21:02.289 --> 21:03.724
No, I will not have them think that.

21:03.725 --> 21:05.060
So you're concerned about how it looks.

21:05.061 --> 21:06.563
I'm concerned about them.

21:06.564 --> 21:08.333
I have been trying so
hard to win them back,

21:08.334 --> 21:09.670
to not have them hate me anymore.

21:09.671 --> 21:10.939
Well, it is hardly my fault

21:10.940 --> 21:12.943
that you spent years
as an absent father.

21:12.944 --> 21:15.682
- Don't throw that in my face!
- And why shouldn't I?

21:15.683 --> 21:18.186
Why should I pay again
for your selfishness?

21:18.187 --> 21:20.090
(DOOR SLAMS)

21:20.091 --> 21:20.926
What was that?

21:21.928 --> 21:23.765
I'll check the children.

21:26.504 --> 21:29.443
(ENGINE REVVING)

21:29.444 --> 21:31.280
(TIRES SQUEALING)

21:33.117 --> 21:35.121
John? Stop!

21:38.962 --> 21:41.633
(GEARS GRINDING)

21:41.634 --> 21:43.169
John, what are you doing?

21:43.170 --> 21:45.173
I don't want to hear it!

21:45.174 --> 21:46.242
I'm sick of your arguing!

21:46.243 --> 21:48.849
Okay, okay. Just come here.

21:53.090 --> 21:56.096
(JOHNNY SOBBING)

22:04.112 --> 22:07.352
Look, I am so sorry, John,
that you had to hear that.

22:08.822 --> 22:12.027
All we were doing is
trying to sort out...

22:12.028 --> 22:13.831
I know what you were sorting out.

22:13.832 --> 22:16.369
But I'm not moving.

22:16.370 --> 22:20.077
I'm staying in St. Louis with you.

22:20.078 --> 22:22.181
With... with me?

22:22.182 --> 22:23.985
It's the right thing to do.

22:25.354 --> 22:28.227
The right thing? For whom?

22:30.432 --> 22:31.700
JOHNNY: You don't have friends.

22:31.701 --> 22:33.738
You won't have Mom, and...

22:35.374 --> 22:37.912
if I leave,

22:37.913 --> 22:39.549
you'll have no one.

22:39.550 --> 22:41.887
You'll be all alone.

22:41.888 --> 22:44.427
So that's why you want to stay?

22:45.762 --> 22:48.734
No one, not even you, deserves

22:48.735 --> 22:50.539
to be alone like that.

23:05.402 --> 23:07.773
Well, you should know...

23:10.178 --> 23:11.613
that I'm not gonna be alone.

23:11.614 --> 23:13.552
I do have someone.

23:15.021 --> 23:17.926
Virginia.

23:17.927 --> 23:19.963
Aunt Gini?

23:19.964 --> 23:21.700
What do you mean?

23:21.701 --> 23:26.109
I mean we're-we're together. In love.

23:27.479 --> 23:30.083
We're, uh... we're gonna get married.

23:30.084 --> 23:32.956
Look, I know that must
seem strange to you,

23:32.957 --> 23:35.628
given all the years that Aunt Virginia

23:35.629 --> 23:37.164
has been a part of our family

23:37.165 --> 23:38.801
and how close you've been to Tessa.

23:38.802 --> 23:41.741
This whole time,
you've-you've loved her?

23:42.810 --> 23:44.178
I did.

23:44.179 --> 23:45.681
How could you do that?

23:45.682 --> 23:47.485
Look, what you have
to understand is that

23:47.486 --> 23:49.689
the last thing I wanted
was to hurt your mother.

23:49.690 --> 23:51.693
But you did. Why?

23:51.694 --> 23:56.436
Because grown-up lives are
just impossibly complicated.

23:56.437 --> 23:59.876
Because I loved Virginia,
and as much as I tried,

23:59.877 --> 24:01.980
I just couldn't change that feeling.

24:01.981 --> 24:04.986
Well, then you-you weren't
trying hard enough.

24:04.987 --> 24:06.657
I was, John.

24:06.658 --> 24:08.293
Look, I'm... look, I'm not
saying I'm blameless.

24:08.294 --> 24:09.328
It's far from it.

24:09.329 --> 24:11.900
I have made many mistakes,

24:11.901 --> 24:14.339
but that doesn't mean
there isn't love in it.

24:15.341 --> 24:16.910
I love you...

24:16.911 --> 24:18.514
and Jenny and Howie.

24:18.515 --> 24:22.522
And I did love your mother. I still do.

24:22.523 --> 24:26.431
But not in that way.

24:28.468 --> 24:30.772
No. No, that way...

24:32.476 --> 24:35.448
that's how I love Virginia.

24:35.449 --> 24:38.854
So the good news is, you
don't have to stay here

24:38.855 --> 24:41.393
because you're worried about me.

24:42.395 --> 24:45.166
I won't, then.

24:45.167 --> 24:49.008
Mom will really need my help
if we're moving so far away.

24:51.547 --> 24:53.217
You know, John...

24:57.893 --> 25:01.833
you don't have to feel so
responsible for adults.

25:01.834 --> 25:05.007
Let them figure out their
problems for themselves.

25:06.844 --> 25:09.182
You can just be a boy.

25:12.388 --> 25:13.525
No.

25:14.960 --> 25:16.363
I really can't.

25:30.357 --> 25:31.526
(GROANS)

25:31.527 --> 25:33.329
I've been looking everywhere for you.

25:33.330 --> 25:37.872
A mai tai is made from pineapple,
limes, and cherries...

25:37.873 --> 25:39.843
maraschino, but still.

25:39.844 --> 25:41.447
It's practically a health drink.

25:42.883 --> 25:45.788
Is Daddy upstairs in the room?

25:45.789 --> 25:47.090
No, he's off somewhere,

25:47.091 --> 25:49.863
planning his new life
as an old bachelor.

25:49.864 --> 25:53.035
Mom, I'm-I'm so sorry.

25:53.036 --> 25:57.645
- I can't imagine...
- What a relief it is?

25:57.646 --> 25:59.147
You don't mean that.

25:59.148 --> 26:01.419
No one understands their parents.

26:01.420 --> 26:03.524
Doesn't matter what age they are.

26:03.525 --> 26:06.997
They always look at them from
the point of view of a child.

26:06.998 --> 26:08.433
Look, I understand that you're upset,

26:08.434 --> 26:10.203
and I am here to support you,

26:10.204 --> 26:13.777
and yes, you and Daddy,
you had a bad day,

26:13.778 --> 26:16.616
but that doesn't
necessarily mean the end.

26:16.617 --> 26:18.386
The one thing that your father and I

26:18.387 --> 26:21.726
do agree on at the
moment is our bafflement

26:21.727 --> 26:25.200
over why you are so determined
to keep us together.

26:27.238 --> 26:29.943
Fine. You want to know one reason?

26:29.944 --> 26:31.746
Bill and I are getting married.

26:31.747 --> 26:33.717
We want to have the ceremony next month.

26:33.718 --> 26:37.324
Now, obviously, we'd like
you and Daddy to be there.

26:37.325 --> 26:39.629
Maybe both of you can
walk me down the aisle.

26:39.630 --> 26:41.633
Apparently, that's in fashion lately,

26:41.634 --> 26:45.641
according to Guy, my wedding planner.

26:45.642 --> 26:47.143
That's a mistake, honey.

26:47.144 --> 26:49.582
He says everybody has a
wedding planner now.

26:49.583 --> 26:51.419
I meant getting married.

26:51.420 --> 26:54.257
For decades, I have tended
to your father's needs,

26:54.258 --> 26:57.765
and the truth is, I am done with sex.

26:57.766 --> 26:59.869
I have been for years.

26:59.870 --> 27:03.109
The thought that I can
now crawl into bed

27:03.110 --> 27:05.914
without being poked and pawed...

27:05.915 --> 27:09.989
just me, alone, with a book, in peace...

27:09.990 --> 27:12.127
This from the woman that told me

27:12.128 --> 27:14.131
to "nail Bill down,"

27:14.132 --> 27:16.001
I believe were your words.

27:16.002 --> 27:18.473
I was speaking from fear,
which I no longer have.

27:18.474 --> 27:20.911
- Oh.
- And really, Virginia.

27:20.912 --> 27:24.184
Given your age and all
you've been through,

27:24.185 --> 27:28.126
do you really need another
failed marriage on your ledger?

27:32.502 --> 27:36.041
Forty years tossed on the trash heap.

27:36.042 --> 27:38.013
And she was happy.

27:39.182 --> 27:40.984
Or drunk.

27:40.985 --> 27:43.355
I wouldn't take anything she
said tonight as gospel.

27:43.356 --> 27:45.961
Oh, you didn't hear her.

27:45.962 --> 27:48.065
You know, between imagining

27:48.066 --> 27:51.506
my parents at the wedding

27:51.507 --> 27:54.211
and cleaning up the mess
that Nancy left behind,

27:54.212 --> 27:56.649
maybe we should push the
wedding down the road a bit...

27:56.650 --> 27:58.252
six months...

27:58.253 --> 28:02.160
when planning it doesn't
feel so overwhelming.

28:02.161 --> 28:04.097
Then let's not plan.

28:04.098 --> 28:05.968
Let's do it tomorrow.

28:05.969 --> 28:07.471
I'm serious.

28:07.472 --> 28:10.511
Just us. Not tell a soul.

28:10.512 --> 28:13.315
- No, we can't do it that way.
- Why not?

28:13.316 --> 28:18.325
Because it's as if we have
walked across broken glass,

28:18.326 --> 28:21.466
barefoot, for years,
to get to this point.

28:21.467 --> 28:24.070
We-we have to celebrate
after all that...

28:24.071 --> 28:28.481
We only have to do what we want.

28:30.985 --> 28:32.588
Look around us, Virginia.

28:32.589 --> 28:35.159
My-my kids are moving
halfway across the country.

28:35.160 --> 28:38.332
Your parents' marriage is falling apart.

28:38.333 --> 28:40.236
People we trusted have betrayed us.

28:40.237 --> 28:43.375
What do we really have
but for each other?

28:43.376 --> 28:44.946
Of course we have each other, but...

28:44.947 --> 28:48.252
So why shouldn't our
marriage reflect that?

28:48.253 --> 28:51.225
Because our marriage

28:51.226 --> 28:55.132
is something bigger than that.

28:55.133 --> 28:58.707
Everything that we've
dedicated ourselves to,

28:58.708 --> 29:01.713
everything that we've believed in,

29:01.714 --> 29:05.587
has all come true for the
couple that started it all.

29:05.588 --> 29:08.225
That'll be so inspiring to people.

29:08.226 --> 29:10.063
I don't... I don't care about people.

29:11.567 --> 29:14.371
We are getting married.
Bill and Virginia.

29:14.372 --> 29:18.613
Not Masters and Johnson,
the famous sex therapists.

29:18.614 --> 29:21.351
If we don't learn to separate
ourselves from that...

29:21.352 --> 29:23.022
No, of course. I want that too.

29:23.023 --> 29:24.892
I-I want to keep that sacred.

29:24.893 --> 29:27.598
Doesn't it say everything
about who we are now,

29:27.599 --> 29:30.036
who we want to be in the future,

29:30.037 --> 29:32.775
if we just push aside
all the distractions

29:32.776 --> 29:36.950
and stand before a clerk,
in the eyes of God,

29:36.951 --> 29:40.824
and make this about us?

29:40.825 --> 29:44.833
Just you and me. Nobody else.

29:48.474 --> 29:51.244
Well, not even Barton?

29:51.245 --> 29:52.848
We still need a witness.

29:52.849 --> 29:54.652
All right, Barton can still witness,

29:54.653 --> 29:56.589
but he's the only one.

29:56.590 --> 29:59.595
<i>♪ Soft piano music ♪</i>

29:59.596 --> 30:00.964
<i>♪♪♪</i>

30:00.965 --> 30:02.635
Just us.

30:06.877 --> 30:08.848
Against the world.

30:10.718 --> 30:15.728
<i>♪♪♪</i>

30:30.925 --> 30:32.528
I can't tell if you're an apparition

30:32.529 --> 30:34.364
or if it's really you.

30:34.365 --> 30:37.236
Well, you've been living
with a ghost for so long.

30:37.237 --> 30:38.740
How could you know?

30:38.741 --> 30:42.715
I forgot my high school
wrestling trophies.

30:45.253 --> 30:47.692
For some reason, they
suddenly mattered to me.

30:48.761 --> 30:50.029
I'll be honest.

30:50.030 --> 30:52.601
I didn't think you had this in you.

30:52.602 --> 30:54.472
Betraying me to Bill and Virginia,

30:54.473 --> 30:58.312
cleaning me out of house and home...

30:58.313 --> 31:00.216
You're impressed.

31:00.217 --> 31:01.787
And sad.

31:04.426 --> 31:07.598
That was my child too, Nancy.

31:07.599 --> 31:09.400
I know you can't love me...

31:09.401 --> 31:14.411
you don't have it in you...
but, God damn it,

31:14.412 --> 31:18.085
I could've finally found
love with a child,

31:18.086 --> 31:20.389
and you took that from me.

31:20.390 --> 31:22.427
It's not like Barton to tattle.

31:22.428 --> 31:24.865
He didn't. I heard you on the tape.

31:24.866 --> 31:26.969
So you eavesdropped.

31:26.970 --> 31:29.475
You really are turning over a new leaf.

31:29.476 --> 31:33.816
I will never again swallow
everything I am...

31:33.817 --> 31:37.824
everything I feel, everything I want...

31:37.825 --> 31:39.896
for the sake of someone else.

31:42.902 --> 31:45.507
You are wrong about one thing.

31:45.508 --> 31:47.009
I, um...

31:47.010 --> 31:49.481
I do love you.

31:49.482 --> 31:53.523
What I just couldn't imagine
was me with a child.

31:53.524 --> 31:55.460
What kind of mother would I be?

31:55.461 --> 31:58.032
Like Virginia? God forbid, maybe worse?

31:59.669 --> 32:01.940
I could've loved a child
for the both of us.

32:03.644 --> 32:06.281
New York can still be
a fresh start for us.

32:06.282 --> 32:08.051
Maybe you can convince me I wouldn't be

32:08.052 --> 32:10.156
such a bad mother after all.

32:11.627 --> 32:15.165
Oh, God. I don't want this, Art.

32:15.166 --> 32:17.438
I'm a shrink, Nance.

32:19.643 --> 32:23.115
You confessed the one thing you
knew would end our marriage

32:23.116 --> 32:25.688
in a room you knew was being taped.

32:27.925 --> 32:30.296
Sometimes what we want

32:30.297 --> 32:32.000
can surprise even us.

32:46.563 --> 32:48.365
I assumed you called me in

32:48.366 --> 32:50.570
because of my last session with Cherlyn,

32:50.571 --> 32:52.173
which was very successful.

32:52.174 --> 32:53.976
This isn't about your last session.

32:53.977 --> 32:55.847
Or your time here as a patient.

32:55.848 --> 32:58.051
This is about your work
with us as our publisher.

32:58.052 --> 33:00.055
Our relationship to Little, Brown.

33:00.056 --> 33:02.527
Which we assumed was an
exclusive relationship,

33:02.528 --> 33:05.099
in that we've given you the
rights to all our work.

33:05.100 --> 33:08.205
And in entrusting our work to you,

33:08.206 --> 33:12.514
we assumed it would engender
a loyalty between us,

33:12.515 --> 33:14.050
one that went both ways.

33:14.051 --> 33:16.555
Of course it does. Both ways.

33:16.556 --> 33:20.028
Then there's something you
have to explain to us, Bob.

33:20.029 --> 33:22.667
Why is it that you've agreed
to do a book on homosexuality

33:22.668 --> 33:24.071
with Art and Nancy?

33:25.073 --> 33:28.079
Did they say that?

33:30.484 --> 33:31.986
How perfectly indiscreet.

33:31.987 --> 33:35.894
We are both your clients
and your doctors, Bob,

33:35.895 --> 33:38.766
and since we're the ones
that agreed to treat you...

33:38.767 --> 33:40.403
Essentially cured you

33:40.404 --> 33:42.541
so you could have a future with Cherlyn.

33:42.542 --> 33:44.578
Although Art did put in the work.

33:44.579 --> 33:46.214
I mean, day-to-day.

33:46.215 --> 33:49.788
Art is not a known entity
in the publishing world.

33:49.789 --> 33:50.957
Nor is Nancy.

33:50.958 --> 33:52.928
Not that they'll be doing a book

33:52.929 --> 33:54.431
or doing anything together now.

33:54.432 --> 33:55.934
What? No.

33:55.935 --> 33:57.537
MASTERS: The point is...

33:57.538 --> 34:00.075
Masters and Johnson are
the household name.

34:00.076 --> 34:02.313
We're the ones with a track
record in sex therapy,

34:02.314 --> 34:04.350
the ones that can, with authority,

34:04.351 --> 34:06.020
publish a book that chronicles

34:06.021 --> 34:08.594
the successful transitioning
of homosexuals.

34:10.163 --> 34:12.935
So your book on homosexuals
would include conversion?

34:15.340 --> 34:18.245
Yes. Conversion.

34:18.246 --> 34:21.753
With the anonymous patient zero
as our first success story.

34:22.955 --> 34:25.225
So do we have your word?

34:25.226 --> 34:27.295
You're the ones the world
wants to hear from,

34:27.297 --> 34:28.699
so yes, of course.

34:28.699 --> 34:30.570
The book is yours.

34:30.571 --> 34:32.974
I'm not sure how this
little mix-up happened

34:32.975 --> 34:35.312
in the first place.

34:35.313 --> 34:39.922
<i>♪♪♪</i>

34:39.922 --> 34:42.126
You know we can't begin to deliver

34:42.127 --> 34:43.462
on conversion therapy.

34:43.463 --> 34:45.733
I said what was needed
to get the book back.

34:45.734 --> 34:47.469
So we'll give him a few days,

34:47.471 --> 34:49.641
and then I'll check in with
Ketterman at Little, Brown,

34:49.641 --> 34:51.446
make sure Bob kept his promise.

34:53.684 --> 34:56.455
I should get home.

34:56.456 --> 34:57.825
Get changed.

35:02.935 --> 35:04.271
Marriage license?

35:05.774 --> 35:07.377
Safe and sound.

35:09.415 --> 35:11.284
We should probably just meet there

35:11.285 --> 35:13.221
instead of you picking me up.

35:13.222 --> 35:16.127
Oh, you don't want me to see
you before the ceremony?

35:16.128 --> 35:18.432
It's bad luck.

35:18.433 --> 35:20.770
I saw my other husbands
before those weddings,

35:20.771 --> 35:23.241
and this one is going to be different.

35:23.242 --> 35:24.343
Mm-hmm.

35:24.344 --> 35:25.847
(DOOR OPENS)

35:25.848 --> 35:28.452
Oh. So sorry, lovebirds.

35:28.453 --> 35:30.923
But I just got off the
phone with Hef's office,

35:30.924 --> 35:32.694
and good news.

35:32.695 --> 35:36.468
He has generously offered up
his mansion for your wedding.

35:36.469 --> 35:38.104
Apparently, Soupy Sales
got married there,

35:38.105 --> 35:40.308
and they released a dozen
white doves into the air

35:40.309 --> 35:42.447
when he kissed his bride.

35:42.448 --> 35:45.887
Why don't we just put a pin
in this for a moment, Guy?

35:45.888 --> 35:50.897
Yeah, Virginia and I are
discussing a smaller affair.

35:50.898 --> 35:53.302
Well, not too small for doves, I hope.

35:54.739 --> 35:56.809
We can still consider doves.

35:56.810 --> 35:58.244
Let's just talk about it tomorrow.

35:58.245 --> 35:59.981
I'll be here.

35:59.982 --> 36:01.586
With bells on.

36:04.124 --> 36:07.430
- He's going to be crushed.
- Mm-hmm.

36:07.431 --> 36:09.969
Maybe I can give him my bouquet.

36:15.514 --> 36:17.015
Dr. Dreessen, you're here.

36:17.016 --> 36:18.719
I wasn't sure you'd get my message.

36:18.720 --> 36:21.190
Well, you made it sound important, so...

36:21.191 --> 36:22.628
Yes, it is.

36:23.663 --> 36:25.566
So...

36:25.567 --> 36:27.002
can I buy you a drink?

36:27.003 --> 36:29.574
I don't think so, no, but thank you.

36:29.575 --> 36:33.416
Okay. You mind if I keep drinking?

36:35.319 --> 36:37.490
All right. Well. (CLEARS THROAT)

36:37.491 --> 36:39.594
As is always the way with these things,

36:39.595 --> 36:43.702
nothing is ever easy... in
life, in love, in business...

36:43.703 --> 36:45.907
You're going to do the
homosexuality book

36:45.908 --> 36:48.044
with Bill and Virginia.

36:48.045 --> 36:51.083
Boy, can you ever read me.

36:51.084 --> 36:54.056
Look, I know I promised
the book to you, and...

36:54.057 --> 36:56.394
You should do the book with them.

36:56.395 --> 36:57.964
I'm moving on.

36:57.965 --> 36:59.901
I'm leaving this work
and the clinic behind.

36:59.902 --> 37:04.143
I'm very sad to hear that.

37:04.144 --> 37:07.417
You're such a gifted doctor.
Dedicated...

37:07.418 --> 37:09.654
I would say the credit is all yours.

37:09.655 --> 37:11.592
Yours and Cherlyn's.

37:11.593 --> 37:14.029
Cherlyn is happy, of course.

37:14.030 --> 37:17.670
Not that she's ever entirely
pleased with anything.

37:17.671 --> 37:19.875
But you know how that goes with women.

37:19.876 --> 37:23.717
I understand you and Nancy
are having difficulties.

37:25.587 --> 37:27.690
Well, it's...

37:27.691 --> 37:30.597
it's not so difficult
once it's finally over.

37:31.466 --> 37:33.301
Ah.

37:33.302 --> 37:37.710
Well, that wife of yours...
tough stuff, huh?

37:37.711 --> 37:39.648
I noticed it in the office.

37:39.649 --> 37:43.121
A beauty, surely, but also a certain

37:43.122 --> 37:45.058
way of the executioner about her...

37:45.059 --> 37:47.262
I'd rather not talk about Nancy.

37:47.263 --> 37:48.966
The wounds are still fresh.

37:48.967 --> 37:51.905
Ugh, I know those wounds.

37:51.906 --> 37:56.815
What I'm saying is, we
understand each other, Art.

37:56.816 --> 38:01.826
And I am so very sorry.

38:03.430 --> 38:05.298
Um...

38:05.299 --> 38:07.036
excuse me for a moment.

38:16.622 --> 38:18.492
Jesus, Bob.

38:18.493 --> 38:19.795
You startled me.

38:27.845 --> 38:30.917
I'm afraid I am tipsy.

38:33.188 --> 38:35.593
I'm afraid it's more than that.

38:35.594 --> 38:37.295
LIBBY: Of course I was
gonna tell you, Bram.

38:37.296 --> 38:39.299
There's just been a million
details to attend to.

38:39.300 --> 38:41.337
I don't even rank as a
last-minute detail?

38:41.338 --> 38:43.876
No, it's just been such
a whirlwind is all.

38:43.877 --> 38:46.047
One minute, I'm sitting
there in the mud,

38:46.048 --> 38:47.717
talking to Dr. Phillips, and then...

38:47.718 --> 38:50.321
God, why did I let you
go to this concert?

38:50.322 --> 38:52.827
All that came from that debacle was VD,

38:52.828 --> 38:55.231
a field full of cows that won't milk,

38:55.232 --> 38:57.135
and you moving 2,000 miles away.

38:57.136 --> 38:59.306
To go to law school.

38:59.307 --> 39:01.077
I thought you would be proud of me.

39:01.078 --> 39:02.379
I am proud of you.

39:02.380 --> 39:04.617
I also love you, so I'm just wondering

39:04.618 --> 39:07.355
how we're gonna continue
seeing each other.

39:07.356 --> 39:08.759
I don't know.

39:08.760 --> 39:10.328
What do you mean, you don't know?

39:10.329 --> 39:12.332
So what are you saying?
That's it? We're done?

39:12.333 --> 39:14.303
I'm not really saying anything.

39:14.304 --> 39:15.973
Why do we have to define it?

39:15.974 --> 39:18.211
Why do you have to sound like a
damn hippie all of a sudden?

39:18.212 --> 39:20.048
I'm just trying to be realistic.

39:20.049 --> 39:23.889
If we find our way to each other, great.

39:23.890 --> 39:28.131
If we don't, it wasn't meant to be.

39:28.132 --> 39:32.006
We have had a wonderful time together.

39:36.983 --> 39:39.487
No. I can't let you go like this.

39:39.488 --> 39:44.497
Oh. Here is the beauty
of the situation, Bram.

39:44.498 --> 39:48.405
It's not up to you whether I stay or go.

39:48.406 --> 39:51.444
The days of me organizing
my life around a man

39:51.445 --> 39:53.749
are over.

39:53.750 --> 39:57.355
Then I'll organize my life around yours.

39:57.356 --> 40:00.863
Unless you can stand there
and honestly tell me

40:00.864 --> 40:03.436
you don't love me.

40:06.409 --> 40:11.116
I would say the evidence
points to my loving you.

40:11.117 --> 40:13.589
Then the defense rests.

40:13.590 --> 40:15.091
For the time being only.

40:15.092 --> 40:18.899
You go and do what you need to do.

40:18.900 --> 40:22.138
But one day, you will look up

40:22.139 --> 40:25.412
from your disgusting tempeh burger,

40:25.413 --> 40:28.184
and I will be there.

40:28.185 --> 40:32.192
The man who upended his
whole life for you.

40:32.193 --> 40:35.198
<i>♪ Soft music ♪</i>

40:35.199 --> 40:39.373
<i>♪♪♪</i>

40:39.374 --> 40:40.943
Ms. Virginia, you have a phone call.

40:40.944 --> 40:42.480
I really need to get home, Guy.

40:42.481 --> 40:44.852
- Take a message.
- It sounds important.

40:47.323 --> 40:49.159
VIRGINIA: <i>I'm surprised
to hear from you so soon.</i>

40:49.160 --> 40:50.829
Well, I'm surprised to be calling,

40:50.830 --> 40:52.967
but I wanted to tell you one
last thing before I go.

40:52.968 --> 40:55.806
Oh, no. Is the damage from
Nancy worse than we thought?

40:55.807 --> 40:58.377
Bob Drag just kissed me in a men's room.

40:58.378 --> 40:59.647
He what?

40:59.648 --> 41:01.250
<i>Kissed me in a men's room.</i>

41:01.251 --> 41:03.422
He <i>kissed you,</i> kissed you?

41:03.423 --> 41:04.824
<i>Like Rhett kissed Scarlett.</i>

41:04.825 --> 41:06.795
<i>And so it is my opinion</i>

41:06.796 --> 41:08.297
as a doctor and psychiatrist

41:08.298 --> 41:10.335
that Bob is an active homosexual,

41:10.336 --> 41:13.040
<i>which means if you're
looking for a success story</i>

41:13.041 --> 41:14.877
<i>of retraining sexual impulses</i>

41:14.878 --> 41:18.150
from homosexual to heterosexual,
Bob Drag is not it.

41:18.151 --> 41:22.292
<i>My fear is that it now
negates the book entirely.</i>

41:22.293 --> 41:25.298
Please know the work I did with Bob...
I really did try.

41:25.299 --> 41:26.801
<i>Please convey that to Bill.</i>

41:26.802 --> 41:28.872
Of course. I will tell him.

41:28.873 --> 41:29.875
<i>Bye.</i>

41:35.487 --> 41:40.497
<i>♪♪♪</i>

41:55.125 --> 41:57.863
- Excuse me.
- I'm so sorry.

41:57.864 --> 41:59.801
Oh. Mrs. Johnson.

41:59.802 --> 42:02.205
You're Billy's partner.

42:02.206 --> 42:03.975
I recognized you from your book.

42:03.976 --> 42:05.044
Ah.

42:05.045 --> 42:07.483
Anyway, have a good day.

42:07.484 --> 42:09.888
I will. Thank you.

42:16.502 --> 42:17.771
How do I look?

42:18.840 --> 42:20.175
Sharp as a tack.

42:21.512 --> 42:23.014
Are you going someplace special?

42:24.283 --> 42:26.019
Nope.

42:26.020 --> 42:30.061
Just home. You know. Eventually.

42:30.062 --> 42:33.400
Good, because Dody's here to see you.

42:33.401 --> 42:35.772
I'm pretty sure she
said her name was Dody.

42:35.773 --> 42:38.111
I'm definitely sure she said
she's someone from way back.

42:42.754 --> 42:45.893
DODY: I don't know if you
remember my cousin Delia.

42:45.894 --> 42:47.161
Oh, I don't know.

42:47.162 --> 42:51.136
Uh, dark hair? Had a
very high-pitched...

42:51.137 --> 42:53.475
- Laugh? Yes.
- Yeah.

42:53.476 --> 42:55.244
But a heart of gold.

42:55.245 --> 42:58.083
Anyway, so she just recently
moved to Chesterville,

42:58.084 --> 43:00.288
so I'm staying with her now.

43:00.289 --> 43:01.824
In Chesterville.

43:01.825 --> 43:04.129
- Just right outside...
- St. Louis.

43:04.130 --> 43:07.268
- Yes. About ten...
- Ten minutes.

43:07.269 --> 43:10.374
Oh, Bill, you don't have
to look so worried.

43:10.375 --> 43:12.813
I'm here because...

43:12.814 --> 43:15.719
well, I'm embarrassed about
the last time we met.

43:15.720 --> 43:18.157
Oh. Dody, no. You don't have to...

43:18.158 --> 43:20.394
No, no, I do.

43:20.395 --> 43:25.071
There's nothing worse
than a weepy woman,

43:25.072 --> 43:29.847
and yet seeing you
really did upend things.

43:29.848 --> 43:33.287
- My marriage, for starters.
- Oh, no.

43:33.288 --> 43:36.694
- No, I would never...
- And you can't blame yourself.

43:36.695 --> 43:39.700
It had to happen.

43:39.701 --> 43:44.443
I've been living like a visitor
in my own life for so long.

43:44.444 --> 43:47.650
But seeing each other

43:47.651 --> 43:52.559
also clarified for me another truth...

43:52.560 --> 43:55.966
that it was really always the two of us

43:55.967 --> 43:57.637
that were meant to be together.

44:02.981 --> 44:04.116
I'm, uh...

44:07.122 --> 44:09.093
I'm-I'm getting married.

44:10.496 --> 44:11.831
Oh.

44:11.832 --> 44:15.304
- Today.
- Oh, my goodness.

44:15.305 --> 44:17.676
- To...
- To Virginia.

44:17.677 --> 44:19.447
Virginia? Oh, Johnson.

44:19.448 --> 44:21.884
- Mm.
- Mrs. Johnson.

44:21.885 --> 44:23.955
Oh, I just saw her at the elevator.

44:23.956 --> 44:26.293
You did? You introduced yourself?

44:26.294 --> 44:28.163
Oh, no. No, no.

44:28.164 --> 44:29.867
But I would love to meet her.

44:29.868 --> 44:32.138
I mean, if I'm staying in the area.

44:32.139 --> 44:37.048
Well, perhaps, uh, you know,
someday in the future.

44:37.049 --> 44:40.020
That would be nice.

44:40.021 --> 44:42.726
It would settle things,

44:42.727 --> 44:45.432
once and for all,

44:45.433 --> 44:48.572
to see you happy with someone else.

44:54.216 --> 44:58.558
No one actually knows that
I'm getting married today

44:58.559 --> 45:01.129
except for my old friend Barton.

45:01.130 --> 45:03.601
And now you.

45:03.602 --> 45:06.575
The person I've known
even longer than that.

45:09.748 --> 45:11.984
Wouldn't it be something

45:11.985 --> 45:15.191
if we ended up as friends?

45:15.192 --> 45:17.497
Dody, we already are.

45:29.119 --> 45:30.622
I haven't returned your calls

45:30.623 --> 45:32.626
because I wanted to
speak to you in person.

45:32.627 --> 45:35.130
Lurking in the parking
lot doesn't bode well.

45:35.131 --> 45:37.803
I'm hoping you can say something
to make sense of all this.

45:37.804 --> 45:39.305
Well, you have to know

45:39.306 --> 45:41.276
you're the last person I wanted to hurt.

45:41.277 --> 45:42.479
Just me you're worried about?

45:42.480 --> 45:44.048
What about Art? What about the people

45:44.049 --> 45:45.719
who trusted you enough to hire you?

45:45.720 --> 45:47.255
You know as well as I do

45:47.256 --> 45:49.560
the world of sexual
therapy is exploding.

45:49.561 --> 45:51.062
It's changing by the minute.

45:51.063 --> 45:53.267
Bill and Virginia are trying
to hold on to something

45:53.268 --> 45:54.803
that is already slipping
from their grasp.

45:54.804 --> 45:56.339
That's absurd.

45:56.340 --> 45:58.343
And it won't work, what
you're trying to do.

45:58.344 --> 45:59.813
Of course it will.

45:59.814 --> 46:01.617
I will simply build
on what they started.

46:01.618 --> 46:03.755
Copernicus discovered the Sun
was the center of the universe.

46:03.756 --> 46:05.792
Then Galileo pushed it further.
So did Hubble.

46:05.793 --> 46:08.263
Now Neil Armstrong is
walking on the moon.

46:08.264 --> 46:11.269
I will take their work places
they can only imagine.

46:11.270 --> 46:14.208
They're the top sex
experts in the country,

46:14.209 --> 46:16.279
with years of cutting-edge work ahead.

46:16.280 --> 46:19.920
I'm not saying they won't continue.

46:19.921 --> 46:21.389
You know Virginia better than I.

46:21.390 --> 46:24.563
Her unbridled ambition, her
craving for acclaim...

46:24.564 --> 46:26.968
She is pushing the work,
pushing Bill, even,

46:26.969 --> 46:28.270
into an area now

46:28.271 --> 46:30.608
that may very well be their undoing.

46:30.609 --> 46:31.445
No.

46:31.446 --> 46:33.415
Gay conversion therapy.

46:37.122 --> 46:40.028
And why would I believe
anything you say?

46:43.435 --> 46:45.205
You don't have to believe me.

46:47.209 --> 46:49.012
Investigate for yourself.

46:49.013 --> 46:50.515
I, uh... I strongly suspect

46:50.516 --> 46:52.319
you won't want anything to do with it.

47:12.960 --> 47:16.600
Hello. I'm checking in
for Masters and Johnson.

47:16.601 --> 47:18.136
Both parties here?

47:18.137 --> 47:20.174
Not yet, but I'm sure he'll be here...

47:20.175 --> 47:21.845
Take a seat.

47:35.406 --> 47:36.740
(MASTERS SIGHS)

47:36.741 --> 47:39.312
Oh, leave it to the two men to be late.

47:39.313 --> 47:40.682
Maybe we should take my car

47:40.683 --> 47:42.886
and, uh, head down to
City Hall together.

47:42.887 --> 47:45.357
I'm not going anywhere until
you tell me it's not true.

47:45.358 --> 47:46.861
What's that?

47:46.862 --> 47:48.664
That you and Virginia
are publishing a book

47:48.665 --> 47:50.234
advocating gay conversion.

47:50.235 --> 47:53.941
Uh, Virginia and I took
back from Art and Nancy

47:53.942 --> 47:55.745
what is rightfully ours.

47:55.746 --> 47:58.183
I mean, we will
eventually publish a book

47:58.184 --> 47:59.920
documenting our work on homosexuality,

47:59.921 --> 48:01.389
but we discussed all this.

48:01.390 --> 48:03.127
You promised me, Bill.

48:05.131 --> 48:07.904
And I'm not advocating
conversion therapy, Barton.

48:09.641 --> 48:14.015
(STAMMERING) Is this about Bob Drag?

48:14.016 --> 48:15.250
Because... yes.

48:15.251 --> 48:20.260
It turns out he was able to, uh,

48:20.261 --> 48:22.499
redirect his homosexual impulses

48:22.500 --> 48:24.836
towards his heterosexual
relationship, but...

48:24.837 --> 48:27.174
My goodness. After
everything I suffered.

48:27.175 --> 48:30.582
The years of self-doubt
and self-loathing

48:30.583 --> 48:33.721
and what it did to Margaret and Vivian.

48:33.722 --> 48:36.125
I damn near killed myself
trying to extinguish

48:36.126 --> 48:37.963
the very essence of who I am!

48:37.964 --> 48:39.365
You saw it!

48:39.366 --> 48:44.141
I did, I did, and I hope
to never see it again.

48:44.142 --> 48:48.584
What we are exploring is
nothing like the torture

48:48.585 --> 48:50.153
that you were subjected to.

48:50.154 --> 48:52.324
We simply took what was working

48:52.325 --> 48:54.429
so successfully with
heterosexual couples

48:54.430 --> 48:58.303
and just directed it towards Drag,

48:58.304 --> 49:00.108
to see if it could help.

49:01.310 --> 49:03.179
He begged me, Barton,

49:03.180 --> 49:06.019
and I felt it was my duty
as his doctor to help him

49:06.020 --> 49:08.390
if-if he wanted that change.

49:08.391 --> 49:10.128
We shouldn't have to change.

49:11.965 --> 49:14.436
You're right.

49:14.437 --> 49:17.409
And-and we can discuss
all this on the drive.

49:17.410 --> 49:19.145
I-I'm pretty sure it's bad luck

49:19.146 --> 49:20.615
to keep a bride waiting
on her wedding day.

49:20.616 --> 49:22.318
And I understand it's your bride

49:22.319 --> 49:25.123
that's pushing you toward
this conversion work.

49:25.124 --> 49:28.163
- What?
- Because I'm fond of her, Bill.

49:28.164 --> 49:29.499
I always have been.

49:29.500 --> 49:31.069
But I've also seen over the years

49:31.070 --> 49:33.139
how Virginia has the most to prove,

49:33.140 --> 49:36.447
how hard she fights to advance
her place in the work.

49:36.448 --> 49:38.283
Maybe because she's uncredentialed.

49:38.284 --> 49:39.786
Wait a minute.

49:39.787 --> 49:42.157
You and I can sort out our
differences on conversion,

49:42.158 --> 49:43.928
but if you're gonna malign Virginia...

49:43.929 --> 49:45.498
You stepped too far with this, Bill.

49:45.499 --> 49:46.500
I can't abide it.

49:46.501 --> 49:48.136
Oh, you can't abide it.

49:48.137 --> 49:50.340
Well, I can't have you speak
like this about Virginia.

49:50.341 --> 49:52.144
Then you better head to City Hall alone,

49:52.145 --> 49:54.516
because I will say what's
needed to be said.

49:54.517 --> 49:57.321
I've loved you like a son.

49:57.322 --> 50:00.127
We have a relationship
of nearly 30 years.

50:00.128 --> 50:01.530
But if you pursue this path...

50:01.531 --> 50:03.400
use your bully pulpit

50:03.401 --> 50:06.005
to advocate for the
conversion of homosexuals...

50:06.006 --> 50:09.480
I will make it my life's
work to see you discredited.

50:13.522 --> 50:16.428
William Masters. Virginia Johnson.

50:20.569 --> 50:22.070
Hello again. So, as I said,

50:22.071 --> 50:24.175
Dr. Masters will be here any minute.

50:24.176 --> 50:26.713
The appointment was at 4 p. m.

50:26.714 --> 50:28.551
It's 4:13 now.

50:28.552 --> 50:30.120
Yes, I'm-I'm aware of that,

50:30.121 --> 50:32.726
but if you could just
signal to me instead of...

50:35.866 --> 50:37.535
No, I don't need any tissues.

50:37.536 --> 50:38.771
Not yet.

50:38.772 --> 50:41.477
Remember, we close at 5 p. m.

50:41.478 --> 50:43.379
Sharp.

50:43.380 --> 50:46.454
Dominik DiAngelo. Alison Burke.

50:49.794 --> 50:51.095
Hi.

50:51.096 --> 50:53.299
CLERK: Hello. Can I see your form?

50:53.300 --> 50:54.603
ALISON: Oh, yes. Right here.

50:54.604 --> 50:56.640
CLERK: You have any questions?

50:56.641 --> 51:00.313
<i>♪ Bright guitar music ♪</i>

51:00.314 --> 51:02.652
Think that's it.

51:02.653 --> 51:03.588
Are we ready?

51:03.589 --> 51:05.357
- Whoo!
- Yes!

51:05.358 --> 51:08.097
- Yeah! Let's go! Let's go!
- (LIBBY LAUGHS)

51:14.544 --> 51:17.415
The future is happy and bright,

51:17.416 --> 51:19.486
my sweet boy.

51:19.487 --> 51:21.289
We'll see.

51:21.290 --> 51:22.559
Mm.

51:22.560 --> 51:27.570
<i>♪♪♪</i>

51:58.498 --> 51:59.667
(SIGHS)

52:03.340 --> 52:04.943
MASTERS: Oh.

52:04.944 --> 52:06.446
I was about to leave.

52:06.447 --> 52:09.151
I am so sorry I've kept you waiting.

52:09.152 --> 52:11.155
Where's Barton?

52:11.156 --> 52:15.998
I-I just couldn't deny Guy this moment.

52:15.999 --> 52:18.369
I just want you to know I am so honored

52:18.370 --> 52:20.206
to be your and Dr. Bill's witness.

52:20.207 --> 52:23.514
And while I love a wedding with scale,

52:23.515 --> 52:27.989
I can also embrace the
simple elegance of this.

52:27.990 --> 52:30.226
Guy, could you let the clerk know

52:30.227 --> 52:32.030
that we're here and we're ready?

52:32.031 --> 52:33.033
Right.

52:34.570 --> 52:36.574
(COLLECTIVE SIGH)

52:40.816 --> 52:42.819
We are gathered here in the sight of God

52:42.820 --> 52:44.354
and in the presence of this witness

52:44.355 --> 52:46.325
to join together this man and this woman

52:46.326 --> 52:48.564
in holy matrimony,

52:48.565 --> 52:50.333
which is an honorable estate

52:50.334 --> 52:53.841
and not to be entered into
lightly or unadvisedly

52:53.842 --> 52:56.112
but reverently and discreetly.

52:56.113 --> 52:58.550
William Masters, will
you have this woman,

52:58.551 --> 53:01.690
Virginia Johnson, to be thy wedded wife?

53:01.691 --> 53:03.460
Will you love her, honor her,

53:03.461 --> 53:05.130
keep her in sickness and in health,

53:05.131 --> 53:07.469
forsaking all others, so
long as you both shall live?

53:11.042 --> 53:12.678
I will.

53:12.679 --> 53:15.684
CLERK: Virginia Johnson,
will you have this man,

53:15.685 --> 53:18.389
William Masters, to be
thy wedded husband?

53:18.390 --> 53:20.260
Will you love him, honor him,

53:20.261 --> 53:22.732
keep him in sickness and in health,

53:22.733 --> 53:25.571
forsaking all others, so
long as you both shall live?

53:25.572 --> 53:26.907
I will.

53:26.908 --> 53:28.710
CLERK: Do you pledge to remember

53:28.711 --> 53:30.681
that love, trust, and loyalty alone

53:30.682 --> 53:33.954
will prevail as the foundation
for a happy and enduring home,

53:33.955 --> 53:38.062
which will be full of joy
and will abide in peace?

53:38.063 --> 53:39.532
We do.

53:39.533 --> 53:41.202
We do.

53:41.203 --> 53:43.740
CLERK: By the power vested in
me by the state of Missouri,

53:43.741 --> 53:46.580
I now pronounce you man and wife.

53:46.581 --> 53:49.586
<i>♪ Uplifting music ♪</i>

53:49.587 --> 53:54.597
<i>♪♪♪</i>

54:08.958 --> 54:10.293
Congratulations.

54:10.294 --> 54:12.097
- Thank you.
- CHUCK:  Dr. and Mrs. Masters!

54:12.098 --> 54:13.901
MASTERS: I'm sorry. No,
this is a private affair.

54:13.902 --> 54:15.104
Hey, you! Skedaddle!

54:16.874 --> 54:18.410
How did he know we'd be here?

54:18.411 --> 54:20.748
I have no idea.

54:20.749 --> 54:22.250
Well, don't look at me.

54:22.251 --> 54:24.154
I found out about this 30 minutes ago.

54:24.155 --> 54:25.958
But it was a beautiful ceremony.

54:25.959 --> 54:27.896
And I wish you every happiness.

54:31.303 --> 54:33.339
Maybe there's a back door.

54:33.340 --> 54:35.744
Just in case.

54:35.745 --> 54:37.347
Bill, it's fine.

54:37.348 --> 54:38.952
Come on.

